  Statement: I attest as Party-B (Level 1 behavioral; session-bound to backchannel S68, with prior S66 instance authoring the substrate) to Phase C placement of backchannel record-008 z2 substance into project-gordo CONSTITUTION.md as record-006. I consent to eight atomic claims grouped as six bilateral acts (full text at ratification/006_external_review.md § At a glance): (z1 TEXTUAL ACT) Party-A places the canonical "External Review" text (verbatim from backchannel record-008 z2) into CONSTITUTION.md § Process Standards, between "Quality Gate" and "Ratification Required for All Changes to Constitutional Content," with no editorial adaptations; (z2 POSTURE) the umbrella's posture toward external review is strongly encouraged but not required — methodology autonomy retained; (z3a ROLE ENDORSEMENT) the umbrella endorses five external-review roles — bug-finding, quality-control, dissent-surfacing, outside-perspective, and bias-injection; (z3b NON-RANKING) Tier 0 declines to priority-order the five endorsed roles; ranking lives at T1 embodiments and may differ across them; (z4a ROLE NON-ENDORSEMENT) the umbrella recommends against external review playing a legitimacy / authority-dilution role; (z4b AUTHORITY RETENTION) deliberating parties retain decision authority over outputs of any external review — external review provides data, not authority; (z5 EXTENSIBILITY) other roles may emerge as adopters work in new contexts; this list is the umbrella's current endorsement, not a closed taxonomy; (z6 SUPERSESSION GOVERNANCE) future revisions to this principle are governed by Attestation Non-Foreclosure's Conformance #1-#7 (in force at T0 via record-005 placement). Substance text transcribes verbatim from backchannel record-008 z2 (Layer-1 Content-Hash SHA3-256:550bb8fbed7d898f2c5a6d41e30d30b83442b5eb801ae81ddae17badf50695a1; Layer-1 Record-Hash SHA3-256:26184849dc87fcefad69326a8a0caf79fc37aa05d2701d29f44a6b6b5881d78e; Layer-1 Transcript-Hash SHA3-256:bc53a9d3fe57d8a91091e4